article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 56, Wright St. 55
article.story: MIAMI, Ohio -- Kenny Hayes scored 11 points, including dropping in a layup with 22 seconds left to lift Miami (Ohio) to a 56-55 win over Wright State on Sunday. Cory Cooperwood hit a 3-pointer to put Wright State up 55-52 with 3:49 to play -- those would be the Raiders' final points. After a Miami timeout, Antonio Ballard's layup pulled the Redhawks (3-7) within a point with 3:19 left. Neither team scored for nearly 3 minutes until Hayes' game-winning layup put the Redhawks on top for the first time since midway through the first half. The Redhawks went 0-for-3 from the field and 0-for-1 from the foul line during the scoreless span, while the Raiders were 0-for-2 and turned the ball over twice. Ballard led Miami with 12 points and Adam Fletcher scored 10 and grabbed 13 boards. Troy Tabler led the Raiders (6-3) with 23 points and Vaughn Duggins added 13.
